        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#JP">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><desc>personal name</desc></gap> <supplied reason="lost">ἐπι</supplied><unclear>κα</unclear>λεῖ Τακιμα γυναῖκα
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp><app><note>Text of Nenci</note></app></listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>[name] calls Tamika his wife</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Nenci observes that the letter forms reflect Elymian types. The 'informal' scratched form of the inscription leaves it uncertain what the status of this text might be in relation to the act of burial. An online edition is also available at <ref target="https://saet.sns.it/it/antiquarium-giuseppe-nenci/iscrizione-graffita-e3659/">https://saet.sns.it/it/antiquarium-giuseppe-nenci/iscrizione-graffita-e3659/</ref>.</p>
            </div>
